p\", \"from\": 1060, \"to\": 1070}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There are also half a dozen types of microwave popcorn, sour candy, off-brand boxed macaroni and cheese, jars of \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009chot-dog sausages\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d and Hershey\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s cookies and cream bars.\\u00c2 Again, this is a gourmet grocery store.\\u00c2 As an American, I am offended.\", \"from\": 1073, \"to\": 1323, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1299, \"end\": 1307, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999551551142095, \"rank\": 4.484687892821436e-05, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"half a dozen types\", \"from\": 1088, \"to\": 1106}, {\"ngram\": \"microwave popcorn\", \"from\": 1110, \"to\": 1127}, {\"ngram\": \"sour candy\", \"from\": 1129, \"to\": 1139}, {\"ngram\": \"off-brand\", \"from\": 1141, \"to\": 1150}, {\"ngram\": \"boxed macaroni\", \"from\": 1151, \"to\": 1165}, {\"ngram\": \"cheese\", \"from\": 1170, \"to\": 1176}, {\"ngram\": \"jars\", \"from\": 1178, \"to\": 1182}, {\"ngram\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009chot-dog\", \"from\": 1186, \"to\": 1196}, {\"ngram\": \"\\u00c2\", \"from\": 1248, \"to\": 1249}, {\"ngram\": \"a gourmet grocery store\", \"from\": 1265, \"to\": 1288}, {\"ngram\": \"\\u00c2\", \"from\": 1289, \"to\": 1290}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As a journalist, I am intrigued.\\u00c2 I stop by this area nearly every time I am in the city, hoping to see someone purchase something so I can ask why, but I have never been lucky.\", \"from\": 1324, \"to\": 1502, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a journalist\", \"from\": 1327, \"to\": 1339}, {\"ngram\": \"this area\", \"from\": 1368, \"to\": 1377}, {\"ngram\": \"the city\", \"from\": 1404, \"to\": 1412}, {\"ngram\": \"someone\", \"from\": 1428, \"to\": 1435}, {\"ngram\": \"something\", \"from\": 1445, \"to\": 1454}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Until today, when within a few minutes of lurking I caught sight of a young French woman plucking a package of Reese\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s dipped pretzels from the shelf.\", \"from\": 1503, \"to\": 1655, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1579, \"end\": 1585, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9999994083238494, \"rank\": 5.905362874313656e-07, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"today\", \"from\": 1509, \"to\": 1514}, {\"ngram\": \"a few minutes\", \"from\": 1528, \"to\": 1541}, {\"ngram\": \"sight\", \"from\": 1562, \"to\": 1567}, {\"ngram\": \"a package\", \"from\": 1601, \"to\": 1610}, {\"ngram\": \"Reese\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s\", \"from\": 1614, \"to\": 1623}, {\"ngram\": \"pretzels\", \"from\": 1631, \"to\": 1639}, {\"ngram\": \"the shelf\", \"from\": 1645, \"to\": 1654}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I pounced.\\u00c2 \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cIt\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s a mix of sweet and salty, and Americans love sweet and salty,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d Juliette Sabater, who works in marketing, explains in French.\", \"from\": 1656, \"to\": 1805, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1744, \"end\": 1752, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Juliet\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.215672504084954e-18, \"text\": \"Juliette\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Juliet\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Juliet\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"\\u00c2\", \"from\": 1666, \"to\": 1667}, {\"ngram\": \"a mix\", \"from\": 1678, \"to\": 1683}, {\"ngram\": \"Americans\", \"from\": 1708, \"to\": 1717}, {\"ngram\": \"marketing\", \"from\": 1774, \"to\": 1783}, {\"ngram\": \"French\", \"from\": 1797, \"to\": 1803}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Most of what is on offer here is too sweet for her, she adds.\", \"from\": 1806, \"to\": 1867, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"offer\", \"from\": 1825, \"to\": 1830}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Yes, that is our primary reputation abroad, and it\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s earned:Accordingto a 2015 study by the market research firm Euromonitor, Americans average more than 126 grams of sugar per day, nearly twice the French intake\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094and more than twice the World Health Organization\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s recommendation.\\u00c2 We are perhaps not helping our cause right now with the Krispy Kreme ads throughout the Paris Metro system that bear a photo of a donut with a bite taken out of it, making it look crescent-shaped, and the caption:The best croissant in Paris.\", \"from\": 1869, \"to\": 2399, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2070, \"end\": 2076, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9999994083238494, \"rank\": 5.905362874313656e-07, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 2246, \"end\": 2257, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris_M\\u00e9tro\", \"score\": 0.9999998407884176, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Paris Metro\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris_M\\u00e9tro\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris_M\\u00e9tro\"}, {\"begin\": 2393, \"end\": 2398, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999736247, \"rank\": 2.6813870499566968e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"our primary reputation\", \"from\": 1882, \"to\": 1904}, {\"ngram\": \"it\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s\", \"from\": 1917, \"to\": 1923}, {\"ngram\": \"Accordingto a 2015 study\", \"from\": 1931, \"to\": 1955}, {\"ngram\": \"the market research firm Euro